# When a python file is called it creates a few internal variables. One of them is __name__. If the file is being run directly, then __name__ will be set to "__main__". If the file is being imported as a module, then __name__ will be set to the name of the file (without the .py extension).
# Yhe most used one is __name__
# Tyhe currently executed file __name==__main__ then we can run some code. This is useful for testing and for creating modules that can be imported without running the code.
